1.title: Infestation of the slaughter house car show
1.plot: In this episode we head over to monroe, washington to check out the rat bastards car club infestation of the slaughter house. Interviews with builders at the show and a peek at the pin-up contest. After that we sit down with vincent kustomz owner justin vincent and talk about his 1950 chevrolet pick-up build, his shop and inspiration.

2.title: Fourth annual kustom kulture festival
2.plot: In this episode we check out the fourth annual kustom kulture festival in silverdale, washington. This event has become a staple of the northwest. Interviews with car owners and builders at the show.

3.title: Second annual rebel riot
3.plot: In this episode we head down to tacoma, washington to check out the second rebel riot. Interviews with builders at the show and a sampling of the pin-up contest. Several interviews also include drag racing shots from the billetproof eruption drags in toutle, washington. Original period restored gassers, rat rods, hot rods, a 1967 dodge charger, a patina r/c and several pick-ups are featured.

4.title: Street freak kruzrs car club - performance tech pros grand opening car & bike show
4.plot: In this episode we go to the street freak kruzrs car club - performance tech pros grand opening car and bike show in snohomish, washington. Featured are a 1963 plymouth sport fury, a 1957 ford kustom, a 1967 woody gilmor dragster and a 1962 shorty olds f85 gasser wagon. We also interview builder big tom mcdonald about his 1951 henry j gasser and barry v. Hasson about his 1966 dodge charger.

imdb.plot outline: Go-Kustom TV began airing in the Greater Seattle Area on Public Access in early 2002. Created by musician and film maker D.A. Sebastian, the show features interviews with Northwest fabricators, bands, tattoo artists, pin-ups, burlesque performers, low brow artists and various kustom kulture events.
